'''Alexander Paul Klöpping''' ({{IPA-nl|aːlɛkˈsɑndər pʌul ˈklɵpɪŋ}}; born 21 January 1987) is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] internet [[Entrepreneurship|entrepreneur]] specializing in [[consumer electronics]], [[blog]]ging, and is also a print and online journalist<ref name="De Telegraaf 2010-11-01">{{cite web|url=http://www.telegraaf.nl/dft/nieuws_dft/article20356844.ece|title='Hard werken om Hyves relevant te houden'|date=1 November 2010|publisher=[[De Telegraaf]]|language=Dutch|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223113704/http://www.telegraaf.nl/dft/nieuws_dft/article20356844.ece|archive-date=23 February 2014|accessdate=30 July 2014}}</ref> and speaker.<ref name="MWG">{{cite web|url=http://www.mwg.nl/congres/sprekers-1/alexander-klopping.html|title=Alexander Klöpping - Sprekers - CONGRES|publisher=MWG|language=Dutch|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110522061156/http://www.mwg.nl/congres/sprekers-1/alexander-klopping.html|archive-date=22 May 2011|accessdate=30 July 2014}}</ref> Klöpping studies [[new media]] at the [[University of Amsterdam]] and is a self-described [[nerd]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://spitsnet.nl/nieuws.php/1/14674/online/De_samenleving_ver_nerd_iseert.html |title=De samenleving ver’nerd’iseert |publisher=spitsnet.nl |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090801154301/http://spitsnet.nl/nieuws.php/1/14674/online/De_samenleving_ver_nerd_iseert.html |archivedate=1 August 2009 }}</ref> He is consulted by Dutch-language media for his expertise.<ref>[http://www.ruuddewild.nl/fragmenten/alexander-klopping-over-iphone-wekker/ Alexander Klöpping over iPhone wekker], radiofragment [[Ruud de Wild]]</ref><ref>http://www.mediacourant.nl/?p=95900</ref><ref>'Het voelt alsof ik in een snoepwinkel ben', interview [[Brabants Dagblad]]</ref><ref>Terugblik: De show van woensdag 8 december (2010), ''Coen en Sander Show''</ref><ref>[http://www.volkskrant.nl/vk/nl/2694/Internet-Media/article/detail/1040967/2010/10/27/Imagoschade-T-Mobile-uit-de-lucht-gegrepen.dhtml Imagoschade T-Mobile 'uit de lucht gegrepen'], [[Volkskrant]]</ref><ref>[http://3voor12.vpro.nl/nieuws/2011/februari/3voor12radio-live-het-feest-van-de-democratie.html Het Feest van de Democratie], [[3VOOR12]]</ref> He himself states that his expertise is "relative".<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20110326192317/http://www.depers.nl/entertainment/555924/Ik-ben-geen-autoriteit.html Alexander Klöpping: ‘Ik ben geen autoriteit’], interview De Pers</ref><ref>[http://www.zie.nl/video/ingezonden/MWG-2011-Alexander-Klopping/m1fzx2efq6it Interview] (video), [[Sanoma]]</ref> <!--He has an impressive unique style.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20111020204048/http://www.televizier.nl/artikel/7400/filemon-wesselink-stikjaloers-op-alexander-klopping Filemon Wesselink stikjaloers op Alexander Klöpping]</ref>-->

Klöpping started an online company, ''The Gadget Company'', at 16 years of age. In 2005, he went to the United States to study, for half a year at a university-oriented to the [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic Party]] and another half year at one oriented towards the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]] and participated in [[political campaign]]s of both parties. He wrote a [[thesis]] about the [[Barack Obama]] campaign. Starting in March 2008, he wrote for Dutch financial journalist Jort Kelder's website ''925.nl'', became editor a few months later and stayed in that position until June 2009.{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}

He also writes articles for Dutch media Emerce, [[NU.nl]], [[NRC Next]] (once every two weeks on Wednesdays), [[Vrij Nederland]], [[Omroep NTR|NTR]] Schooltv<ref>[http://www.schooltv.nl/eigenwijzer/project/3153602/economie-voor-het-vmbo/ Economie voor het VMBO] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120530215858/http://www.schooltv.nl/eigenwijzer/project/3153602/economie-voor-het-vmbo/ |date=30 May 2012 }}, NTR School TV</ref> and [[STER]] Nieuws.{{clarify|date=June 2015|reason=Unclear how he could have written articles for television NTR and STER.}}

Klöpping has been working on Dutch television since 2009. He produced and presented Internet news for ''Bij ons in de BV'' and ''NTR School TV''. He is best known for appearing regularly as a technology expert on the talk show [[De Wereld Draait Door]].<ref>Kijktip | De Wereld Draait Door, interview Televizier</ref> There, he has demonstrated items including the [[iPad]] and [[Kinect]], and commented on the rise of [[social media]], [[WikiLeaks]], the [[Anonymous (group)|Anonymous]] [[cyber-attack]]s, and [[Facebook]] [[privacy policy]]. He is an advisor for Mediafonds<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20100131005913/http://www.mediafonds.nl/page/51245/adviseurs Adviseurs Mediafonds]</ref> and member of the jury on ''TV Lab''.<ref>“Democratische televisie” Alexander Klöpping (Vakjury) over de TV Lab Kijkerspitch, TV Lab</ref>

In 2011, he published the book ''Wikileaks, alles wat je niet mocht weten'' ("Wikileaks, everything you weren't allowed to know").

In 2013, he joined the Committee of Recommendation of Dutch whistleblower foundation [https://publeaks.nl/ Publeaks] that launched a [[Whistleblower|whisteblowing initiative]] in September 2013 based on the [[GlobaLeaks]] software.<ref>{{cite web|title=Vanaf vandaag: anoniem lekken naar media via doorgeefluik Publeaks|url=http://www.volkskrant.nl/vk/nl/2694/Tech-Media/article/detail/3506349/2013/09/09/Vanaf-vandaag-anoniem-lekken-naar-media-via-doorgeefluik-Publeaks.dhtml|publisher=volkskrant.nl|accessdate=22 February 2014}}</ref>

In 2013, Klöpping founded the Universiteit van Nederland ("University of the Netherlands"), that organizes and publishes lectures. That year, Klöpping himself taught three classes on the television series ''DWDD University'' about the history, present and future of [[Silicon Valley]]. Klöpping is a co-founder of [[Blendle]], a platform with articles of thirty major Dutch newspapers and magazines. At Blendle, launched in April 2014, readers pay per article.{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}

